<i>Saint Jerome</i> <small>by <a href="/wiki/Lucas_van_Leyden" title="Lucas van Leyden">Lucas van Leyden</a></small></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="2" class="title" style="text-align:center; background-color:gold;">Priest, Confessor, and Doctor of the Church</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Born</th>
<td>c. 340-347, <a href="/wiki/Stridon" title="Stridon" class="mw-redirect">Stridon</a>, on the border of <a href="/wiki/Dalmatia_(Roman_province)" title="Dalmatia (Roman province)">Dalmatia</a> and <a href="/wiki/Pannonia" title="Pannonia">Pannonia</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Died</th>
<td>420, <a href="/wiki/Bethlehem" title="Bethlehem">Bethlehem</a>, <a href="/wiki/Judea" title="Judea">Judea</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Venerated in</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Roman_Catholic_Church" title="Roman Catholic Church">Roman Catholic Church</a><br />
<a href="/wiki/Eastern_Orthodoxy" title="Eastern Orthodoxy" class="mw-redirect">Eastern Orthodoxy</a><br />
<a href="/wiki/Anglican_Communion" title="Anglican Communion">Anglican Communion</a><br />
<a href="/wiki/Lutheranism" title="Lutheranism">Lutheranism</a><br />
<a href="/wiki/Oriental_Orthodoxy" title="Oriental Orthodoxy">Oriental Orthodoxy</a></td>
